Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.63,0:00:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Oh, Corinna."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.80,0:00:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Why was your letter so short?"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.57,0:00:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Like Eupolis and his astrology..."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.52,0:00:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You tear my heart asunder."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.11,0:00:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"And the pallid color of Idas' gold..."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.50,0:00:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...like the artisans of Galonius..."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.30,0:00:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.49,0:00:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said there is no need to read any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.20,0:00:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, is something...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.37,0:00:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.16,0:00:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.71,0:00:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.75,0:00:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I do something to offend you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.71,0:00:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who can't even pronounce Latin correctly \N don't have the right to read books to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.13,0:00:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.05,0:00:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be more careful from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.72,0:00:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.93,0:02:38.89,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,96)\pos(360,350)}The Thursday Boy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.10,0:02:44.96,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(286,0)\pos(354,323)}University of Munich \N Friedrich Emmanuel School
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.04,0:02:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really got chewed out at the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.42,0:02:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheer up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.01,0:02:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Karl Neumann, Economics major!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.89,0:03:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about me?  Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.62,0:03:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Lotte Frank, a Cultural Anthropology major.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.92,0:03:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you read books to him part time, also?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.25,0:03:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I only take care of his personal needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.86,0:03:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He only has male students read books to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.82,0:03:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in charge of Tuesdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.62,0:03:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On other days, he has other students read \N to him, since he's practically blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.75,0:03:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, so what do you think about the mysterious \N wealthy juggernaut, Hans Georg Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.80,0:03:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.61,0:03:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only jumped at the chance because the pay was good...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.34,0:03:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you heard rumors about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.56,0:03:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say that with a single phone call from his mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.77,0:03:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he can control all the stocks in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.10,0:03:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People call him the Howard Hughes of Bayern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.03,0:03:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has no family.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.94,0:03:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not close with anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.11,0:03:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, his fortune only grows.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.74,0:04:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think he's going to do with all that money?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.32,0:04:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.41,0:04:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there is an even bigger mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.04,0:04:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His other nickname is the Vampire of Bayern.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.29,0:04:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vampire?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.08,0:04:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the bell tolls at 2 AM...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.13,0:04:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he and his butler leave in his hearse like car, \N and they wander the nighttime streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.76,0:04:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like a setting from one \N of those gothic horror stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.22,0:04:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably just taking a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.06,0:04:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Soon I'll be able to confirm if it's just a walk or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.35,0:04:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by "confirm"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.69,0:04:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just for my research paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.81,0:04:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Psychology of Medieval and Present \N Day Financial Figures in Bayern."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.11,0:04:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he'll be the perfect subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.41,0:04:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you did some research on me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.03,0:04:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only looked up your name and major.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.56,0:04:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, just because Schuwald yelled \N at you, don't let it get to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.33,0:04:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has said horrible things to all the other students, also...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.59,0:04:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.71,0:04:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm used to being yelled at and getting hit...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.26,0:04:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're used to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.17,0:05:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.18,0:05:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've had to change foster parents pretty \N often because so much has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.26,0:05:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, you didn't go to \N one of the local schools, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.27,0:05:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you did check up on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.85,0:05:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.42,0:05:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have any parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.98,0:05:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.15,0:05:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I enrolled in the University of Munich \N hoping I could see my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.28,0:05:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, your mother is in Munich?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.55,0:05:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, were you able to see her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.04,0:05:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but it's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.66,0:05:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?  Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.54,0:05:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she's so close!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.13,0:05:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know her name, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.42,0:05:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.46,0:05:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is her name?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.72,0:05:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said I don't care anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.68,0:05:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.26,0:05:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I become curious, I'll find out anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.45,0:05:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Margot...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.89,0:05:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.75,0:05:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She will be easy to find if you know that much!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.63,0:05:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go see her!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.98,0:05:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure your mother will be happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:06:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, it's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.41,0:06:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Margot Langer... Margot Langer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.17,0:06:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The chestnut horse's sprint..."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.34,0:06:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...gathered like thunder in the pond of blood..."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.50,0:06:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...and caused the tide to rise..."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.01,0:06:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't bear to listen to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.13,0:06:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only love that which is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.22,0:06:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't bear to listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.60,0:06:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you tell me something so important?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.40,0:06:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did some research on your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.36,0:06:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.99,0:06:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I said I don't care anymore, get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.03,0:06:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Karl, is there anything I can help you with?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.37,0:06:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.39,0:06:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.08,0:06:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Karl...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.75,0:07:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.21,0:07:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were going to find out what \N Hans Schuwald does at night, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.93,0:07:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I come with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.22,0:07:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.10,0:07:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd feel much better if you came along!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.65,0:07:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.15,0:07:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first major scoop since the founding \N of our Occult Phenomenon Research Society!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.15,0:07:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.84,0:07:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.15,0:07:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this poem was written by one of the founders \N of this university, Bishop Gropius.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.20,0:07:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the poem he wrote in 1502, no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.04,0:07:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is important is this verse right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.50,0:07:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"In the penultimate intercalary year..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.08,0:07:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...the Thursday boy will visit this land."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.15,0:07:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"All books will be engulfed in flame."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.17,0:07:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"And the entire world will be engulfed in sadness."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.82,0:07:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.18,0:07:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the "penultimate intercalary year."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.93,0:07:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's talking abut 1996.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.40,0:08:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it's talking about this year!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.44,0:08:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.07,0:08:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An "intercalary year" is a leap year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.11,0:08:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only leap year left in this century \N are this one and the year 2000.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.87,0:08:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He "will visit this land" and "all books \N will be engulfed in flame."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.29,0:08:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it talks about "all books" and "this land"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.95,0:08:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it means that this university will be burned down!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.66,0:08:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who is the "Thursday boy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.00,0:08:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thursday...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.19,0:08:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The root of Donnerstag is Donner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.19,0:08:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means thunder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.84,0:08:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's talking about a thunder god!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty far fetched!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.35,0:08:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no laughing matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.08,0:08:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This should be the topic of our next issue!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really mind if we print it, \N but who is going to believe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.52,0:08:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That a god of destruction is going \N to come to this university?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.37,0:08:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vampire of Bayern, my ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.77,0:09:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth behind his mysterious outings?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.04,0:09:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about being deluded...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.38,0:09:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet!  They are coming out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.26,0:09:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.51,0:09:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.62,0:09:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.89,0:09:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.77,0:09:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go?  Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.15,0:09:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we shouldn't do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.40,0:09:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this isn't a place for girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.41,0:09:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.20,0:09:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I only love that which is beautiful."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.37,0:09:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.38,0:09:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...just how low that man is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.84,0:09:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.27,0:10:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for a girl, you've \N come to the wrong place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.02,0:10:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I retired a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.61,0:10:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.86,0:10:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you come into someone's place, \N you normally introduce yourself first.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.12,0:10:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.27,0:10:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be a college student...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.88,0:10:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.84,0:10:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I work part time for Mr. Hans Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.13,0:10:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you want with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.72,0:10:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.89,0:10:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know why Mr. Hans Schuwald comes here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.77,0:10:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He comes here for entertainment...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.48,0:10:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is what I'd like to tell you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.85,0:10:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His thing seems to be useless now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.40,0:10:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He comes to hand over money.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.65,0:10:56.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.03,0:10:58.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because when I told him my name...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.87,0:11:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he started to cry and apologize to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.25,0:11:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he fathered my child, and \N then threw me away like trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.88,0:11:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Karl, then you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.65,0:11:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Hans Schuwald's child!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.17,0:11:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.07,0:11:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a lie...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.36,0:11:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.93,0:11:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... are not Margot Langer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.39,0:11:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.43,0:11:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was in the newspaper a year ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.22,0:11:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Former prostitute..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.81,0:11:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Former Prostitute Margot Langer Killed!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.56,0:11:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Killer Currently Unknown."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.69,0:11:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His mother is already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.98,0:11:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are just using that name to become my mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.24,0:11:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to become Margot Langer and swindle \N money from Hans Schuwald!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.96,0:11:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He knows it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.67,0:11:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's paying me, knowing full well that I'm not really her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.21,0:11:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he knows that the real Margot he should \N be paying is no longer of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.49,0:12:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is his way of atonement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.60,0:12:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money!  Money!  Money!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.89,0:12:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For someone who has lived only for money...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.48,0:12:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this is the only way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.29,0:12:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may sound presumptuous of me for saying this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.23,0:12:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People aren't all that different.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.82,0:12:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They would say that you are acting like that old timer's \N son, since he doesn't have much time left...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.97,0:12:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in order to inherit his enormous estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.43,0:12:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys call me a liar, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.17,0:12:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...who knows what YOUR intentions are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.71,0:12:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is one more person...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.90,0:12:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...who claims to be his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.18,0:12:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He came here just like you and \N asked the same questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.64,0:12:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is... impossible...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.36,0:12:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.23,0:12:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is the one who is lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.44,0:12:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows who is lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.57,0:13:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To me, you both look like impostors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.74,0:13:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.35,0:13:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is the same as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.83,0:13:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys take turns reading books to \N Schuwald on different days, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.79,0:13:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.27,0:13:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes that is right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.86,0:13:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the Thursday boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.36,0:13:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell her that you are the real thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.01,0:13:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went through numerous foster parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.66,0:13:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and a lot has happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.04,0:13:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But my current foster parents are really kind to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.77,0:13:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So kind that I would never be able to thank them enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.45,0:13:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why I thought of meeting my real parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.05,0:13:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By knowing how much of a lowlife my real father was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.14,0:13:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I thought I could love my foster parents even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.06,0:13:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was all I wanted...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.99,0:14:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever met this Thursday boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.93,0:14:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm off on Thursdays, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.49,0:14:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but once when I went back to \N get something I had forgotten...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.62,0:14:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've seen him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.37,0:14:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of man is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.54,0:14:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.17,0:14:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has blond hair and a really pretty face...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.70,0:14:31.58,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(200,88)\pos(358,274)}Monday
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.31,0:14:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.85,0:14:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is the Thursday boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.62,0:14:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone at this university is trying to be me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.28,0:14:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen closely to what Mom has to say, okay Karl?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.74,0:14:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this money and take the train on track five.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you get off at the eighth stop, there will \N be a lady named Martha waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.29,0:14:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.91,0:14:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I can't go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are the police after you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.46,0:15:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to stay with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.88,0:15:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.71,0:15:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you stay with me, you'll be put in a foster home!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.63,0:15:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you stay here, people say \N you are the son of a prostitute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.56,0:15:15.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.06,0:15:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about my dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.23,0:15:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's name is Hans Georg Schuwald, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.31,0:15:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.90,0:15:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mrs. Bella from across the street...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.65,0:15:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's rich, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.03,0:15:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said I was abandoned by my father...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.71,0:15:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't abandoned...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.12,0:15:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll go to Dad's place!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.09,0:15:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.19,0:15:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then when?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.88,0:15:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you are older...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.22,0:15:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you still want to meet him after you've grown up...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.64,0:15:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, you mustn't want anything from him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.89,0:15:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't hate him, even if he acts cold towards you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.52,0:15:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.02,0:16:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I don't hate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.28,0:16:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.37,0:16:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father meant to give you this when you were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.73,0:16:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found something, Karl!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.17,0:16:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found out who the Thursday boy is!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.51,0:16:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name is Edmund Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.89,0:16:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is a student in the Literature Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.93,0:16:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without a doubt, he works part time \N at Schuwald's place reading books.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.39,0:16:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he is in charge of Thursdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.69,0:16:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Edmund Fahren...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.42,0:16:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.84,0:16:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like class just ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.70,0:16:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We would like to speak with Edmund Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.04,0:17:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Edmund, are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.16,0:17:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Edmund?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.50,0:17:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't come to class today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.75,0:17:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.92,0:17:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.34,0:17:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a shame...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.47,0:17:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but it's only a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.45,0:17:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are going to get our hands on that swindler!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.60,0:17:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you are the one who is going to \N inherit Schuwald's enormous estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.44,0:17:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.27,0:17:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about the inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.69,0:17:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.74,0:17:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care how much of Schuwald's \N money has been swindled!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.82,0:17:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.91,0:17:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.24,0:17:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... that bastard, Edmund Fahren...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.50,0:17:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't forgive him for calling himself my mom's son!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.82,0:17:55.53,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(371,0)\pos(356,273)}Tuesday
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.09,0:17:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The petals of your silk flowers..."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.63,0:17:57.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...fluttered in the wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.05,0:17:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"So cried the mockingbird within my heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.15,0:18:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't going to say anything today, Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.53,0:18:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you quit after I yelled at you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.55,0:18:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the pay is good?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.87,0:18:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.66,0:18:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not... that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.38,0:18:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you only talk about money?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.34,0:18:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just as you say...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.22,0:18:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are your parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.60,0:18:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... was taken in by foster parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.72,0:18:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me for asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.52,0:18:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want to see your real parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.28,0:18:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.30,0:18:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.57,0:19:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the boy who appeared this \N time may be the real thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.62,0:19:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't after my money...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.96,0:19:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"He"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.00,0:19:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing, I'm just talking to myself.  You may go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.76,0:19:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, also...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.05,0:19:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Latin...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotten much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.06,0:19:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.67,0:19:39.43,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(276,0)\pos(359,271)}Wednesday
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.16,0:19:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Edmund Fahren isn't here today, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.87,0:19:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is probably in bed after catching a cold or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.68,0:19:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow is Thursday, so you don't have to rush around...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.42,0:19:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He will be at Schuwald's place for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.09,0:19:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.80,0:19:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are going to reveal his true nature \N right in front of Schuwald!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.26,0:20:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go all out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.32,0:20:04.78,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{fad\(0,246)\pos(359,272)}Thursday
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.77,0:20:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not showing up...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.52,0:20:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been an hour already...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.56,0:20:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he has a cold, we can always \N attack him while he is in bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.98,0:20:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.67,0:20:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, given our situation, how about \N we barge into his dorm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You even found his address?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.62,0:20:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,204...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.08,0:20:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,204...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,204!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.14,0:20:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.30,0:20:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.89,0:21:13.40,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(359,269)}Friday
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.92,0:21:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a horrible thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.17,0:21:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The entire school is talking about Edmund Fahren now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.88,0:21:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who would have thought he would commit suicide...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.22,0:21:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the school newspaper mentioned \N his suicide note, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.51,0:21:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I can't deceive him anymore."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.06,0:21:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, this must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.15,0:21:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.35,0:21:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he got too close to Schuwald \N by pretending to be his son...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.23,0:21:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he was tortured by his conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.40,0:21:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he was so confused that he would kill himself, he \N shouldn't have done it in the first place...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.83,0:21:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lotte, it must have been difficult yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.37,0:21:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.83,0:22:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police were questioning me the whole day...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.90,0:22:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The part time reading job was canceled today, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.26,0:22:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Schuwald is really upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.84,0:22:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Karl.  Let me introduce you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.43,0:22:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the person in charge of Fridays...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.56,0:22:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.98,0:22:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.23,0:22:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Karl Neumann, an Economics major.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.69,0:22:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Johan Liebert, majoring in law.
